  "message": "Remove transient SQLite WAL/SHM files from sample beads DB fixtures\n\nThese write-ahead log and shared-memory files are ephemeral SQLite\nartifacts that get created when a database is opened and should never\nhave been tracked. They were left behind by previous database\noperations and are now properly cleaned up:\n\n- franken_whisper: beads.db-shm + beads.db-wal\n- frankensqlite: beads.db-wal\n- frankentui: beads.db-wal\n- mcp_agent_mail_rust: beads.db-wal\n- remote_compilation_helper: beads.db-wal\n\nThe actual beads.db files remain intact \u2014 only the transient journal\nfiles are removed.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>",
